<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=dancinstarz426&buddyTimeStamp=20041213&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059845&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Caryn</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Caryn lives at <a href='/home/?user=dancinstarz426'>2168 Young Street</a>, in the exciting neighborhood of Metro Park, which is just outside of downtown Millsberry. She's been living there since July 20th of 2004, and really enjoys being so close to the downtown Entertainment Complex!<br><br>Caryn is a very friendly, easygoing girl who loves to hang out at her best friend's house during evenings and on weekends.  There, they'll often play games while chatting about the cool things they saw after school at the mall that afternoon.<br><br>In addition to being a very athletic girl, Caryn is also a terrific singer, who'll often croon along with her favorite types of music, which include pop, punk, and show tunes.<br><br>Caryn enjoys reading during her more quiet moments, which most likely helped to improve her spelling skills and allowed her to win an impressive Solver trophy!<br><br>On the weekends, Caryn can often be found hanging around the pool with her friends, chatting, splashing, and playing pool games.<br><br>Afterwards it's back to the mall, where she and her friends have recently been admiring the new winter clothes that have just been added to the store. She has already bought a beautiful pink coat, which is one of her favorite colors, and is currently on the lookout for maybe a silver or light blue one, too.<br><br>Just recently, Caryn was awarded a trophy for her wonderful efforts to keep Peabody Park clean and beautiful. She has also received honors in her physical education class for her abilities at Hop-N-Drop, Sink the Three, and Rope Race! Congratulations, Caryn!</div>
